The paper is focused on understanding organizational motivations and approaches towards end user privacy, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of regulatory bodies and the need for effective communication of regulations, which could also fall under the categories of cyber law and policy (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the lack of sustainable solutions for organizational issues related to user privacy, which could be related to software engineering (cs.SE) and computer communications (cs.CC).
